    <completion-notes>REVISED 2026-06-25 (redo): DEPLOYMENT SUCCESSFUL via mcp__dataverse__update_record overlay on sprk_analysisplaybook.sprk_configjson (PB-021 GUID 4369cab2-5f2d-f111-88b5-7ced8d1dc988). Pre-deploy state: 152-char header-only configjson (hourly frequency, no ActionType 52); post-deploy state: 5,096-char full multinode graph (daily 06:00, 5 nodes with LookupUserMembership + sprk_event Task discriminator + membership-scope FetchXml union). statecode=0 (Active) preserved. Verified via post-deploy read_query: ActionType 52 present, sprk_event entity, Task eventtype GUID 124f5fc9-…, membership-scope OR-branch, overdue filter (sprk_duedate OR sprk_finalduedate lt todayUtc), dedupe by sprk_eventid, 5-node graph wired correctly. Spec FR-7 "Dedupe by activityid" wording bug confirmed corrected in repo JSON + deployed configjson to sprk_eventid per CLAUDE.md § '2026-06-25 — Spaarke entity architecture' BINDING rule. AC-7 manual UAT now testable per scenario in notes/smoke/022-tasks-overdue-deploy.md. PB-021 now at parity with PB-020 (task 023), PB-017 (024), PB-022 (025). PRIOR DEFERRAL DISPROVED: the first-attempt hypothesis that runtime engine reads from sprk_playbooknode child rows (not sprk_configjson) was wrong — tasks 011/023/024/025 all successfully overlay configjson via update_record. Historical deferral discussion preserved in smoke notes' "First attempt deferred — reason invalid" section.</completion-notes>
