  <prompt>Edit `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-tasks-overdue.json` (PB-021). Add a parallel branch using `LookupUserMembership` (ActionType 52) so the FetchXml query becomes a union: `(ownerid eq-userid)` OR `(regardingobjectid IN membership-matterIds)`. Dedupe by `activityid`. Redeploy via MCP `update_record` on the existing `sprk_analysisplaybook` row (`sprk_configjson` attribute).</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook designer with expertise in FetchXml union semantics + LookupUserMembership ActionType 52 (ADR-034).</role>

  <goal>`notification-tasks-overdue.json` reflects membership-scope union query. Deployed `sprk_analysisplaybook` row for PB-021 has updated `sprk_configjson` matching the repo file. `jps-validate` passes. Manual UAT confirms AC-7 (user who is `assignedAttorney` on Matter-X but doesn't own any task on it sees overdue tasks on Matter-X).</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-7 (line 142) requires both `notification-tasks-overdue` (PB-021) and `notification-tasks-due-soon` (PB-020) to surface tasks regarding any matter the user is a member of, not just tasks they directly own. The canonical union pattern uses `LookupUserMembership` (ActionType 52, deployed by W0 task series) to resolve the user's matter memberships, then a FetchXml query unions `(ownerid eq-userid)` with `(regardingobjectid IN membership-matterIds)` and dedupes by `activityid`. PB-016 (`notification-new-documents.json`) is the reference example — it already uses LookupUserMembership in this pattern.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-tasks-overdue.json</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-new-documents.json</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-034">Membership resolution via ActionType 52 LookupUserMembership — canonical primitive. Do NOT compose a custom membership query.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Playbook composes JPS primitives only. No new endpoints, no new C# services.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-037">Multinode output composition — fan-out from LookupUserMembership → QueryDataverse → CreateNotification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component Justification not required (modifying existing playbook, not creating a new component).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Dedupe by activityid (FetchXml union may produce duplicates when a user owns a task AND is a member of its regarding matter). Repo JSON file = source-of-truth; deploy from repo, never edit deployed sprk_configjson directly.</constraint>
  </constraints>

