  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load knowledge files. Read spec FR-7 + AC-7.</step>
    <step order="2">Read the reference playbook `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-new-documents.json` (PB-016) to understand the existing LookupUserMembership union pattern.</step>
    <step order="3">Read current `notification-tasks-overdue.json` (PB-021). Document the existing node graph + FetchXml in `notes/`.</step>
    <step order="4">Edit the JSON: add a LookupUserMembership(sprk_matter) node parallel to existing query, then a unified QueryDataverse node with FetchXml: union `(ownerid eq-userid)` OR `(regardingobjectid IN membership-matterIds)`, with distinct/dedupe by activityid.</step>
    <step order="5">Validate via `jps-validate` skill. Fix schema violations.</step>
    <step order="6">Audit via `jps-playbook-audit` skill against deployed Action codes (LookupUserMembership = ActionType 52; ensure SYS-LOOKUP-MEMBERSHIP Action code is referenced).</step>
    <step order="7">Redeploy via `mcp__dataverse__update_record` on `sprk_analysisplaybook` row for PB-021 — set `sprk_configjson` to the new content.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify deployment: `mcp__dataverse__read_query` to fetch PB-021 row + confirm sprk_configjson matches.</step>
    <step order="9">Run tests + build (no C# changes — confirm green): `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 022 status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="11">Document deviations / UAT script in `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp-dataverse">update_record — redeploy playbook sprk_configjson; read_query — verify deployment.</tool>
    <tool name="jps-validate">Schema validation</tool>
    <tool name="jps-playbook-audit">Audit against deployed Action catalog</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-tasks-overdue.json</output>
