  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">notification-tasks-overdue.json node graph includes a LookupUserMembership(sprk_matter) node.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FetchXml unions (ownerid eq-userid) OR (regardingobjectid IN membership-matterIds) with distinct/dedupe on activityid.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">jps-validate passes on the file.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Deployed PB-021 sprk_configjson matches the repo file (verified by read_query).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manual UAT scenario documented for AC-7 verification.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>Spec FR-7 (line 142), AC-7 (line 143). Hint: PB-016 (`notification-new-documents.json`) is the reference example — already does this exact pattern. Hint: the dedupe-by-activityid can be done via `distinct="true"` on FetchXml `&lt;fetch&gt;` element OR via post-query dedupe in the QueryDataverse node config. Hint: this task is parallel-safe with 023, 024, 025 (each owns a different JSON file).</notes>

